# Generated session index (machine-local instance data, rebuilt by `vurctos remember`)
**/sessions/index.db

# Reflection marker (machine-local instance data, managed by `vurctos reflect-apply`)
**/reflections/.last-reflected

# Obsidian per-machine vault config (a project folder doubles as a vault)
.obsidian/

# Python
__pycache__/
*.pyc

# macOS
.DS_Store

# Personal root USER.md (private profile; kept local, not committed to the open-source repo)
/USER.md

# Defense in depth: a real project (with private USER.md / MEMORY.md / sessions)
# should live OUTSIDE this repo, but if one is ever created inside a clone, do
# not let its private memory be staged. The blank template scaffolds are the
# only exception and stay tracked.
**/USER.md
!templates/**/USER.md
**/MEMORY.md
!templates/**/MEMORY.md
**/sessions/*.md
!templates/**/sessions/*.md

# Local repo/source snapshots (never commit; the repo lives on GitHub)
*.bundle
vurctossource.zip
